   {:e #blake3 "73f4788ad988acabe93c780bc29432e5f8510a36cc584e8ce3c687654bda3bbd" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The core self-calibration mechanism. After each harvest, compute the optimal join threshold from the observed cosine distribution using Otsu's method. This is the OBSERVER-4 calibration loop applied to concept parameters.\n\nAPPROACH: Add to concept.rs:\n\npub fn calibrate_join_threshold(store: &Store) -> Option<f32> {\n    // Collect cosine similarities between each observation and its primary concept.\n    // Uses :exploration/concept Ref to find assigned concept, then computes\n    // cosine(observation_embedding, concept_embedding).\n    // Returns None if < 5 observations (insufficient data for calibration).\n    //\n    // Otsu's method: find threshold T in [0.0, 1.0] that minimizes\n    // w_0 * var_0 + w_1 * var_1 (weighted intra-class variance)\n    // where class 0 = similarities below T, class 1 = similarities above T.\n    // Sweep T in steps of 0.01 from 0.10 to 0.90.\n    //\n    // Also compute temperature = stddev(all_similarities) / 2 for sigmoid.\n}\n\nReturns (optimal_threshold, optimal_temperature) as a tuple.\n\nWire into harvest_pipeline (harvest.rs) or the harvest command: after harvest completes, call calibrate_join_threshold. If it returns Some, write :policy/concept-join-threshold and :policy/concept-sigmoid-temperature datoms. The observe command already reads :config/concept.join-threshold (observe.rs:615) — change the config key to :policy/concept-join-threshold for consistency with other policy datoms.\n\nBOOTSTRAP: First 5 observations use embedder.join_threshold() default. After 5+ observations with concept assignments, Otsu takes over. The harvest output should report: 'concept threshold: 0.20 -> 0.47 (calibrated from 12 observations)'.\n\nCONVERGENCE PROPERTY: As N increases, the Otsu threshold converges to the natural decision boundary of the embedding space for THIS project's domain. Different projects converge to different values. This is C9 compliance.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: CAL-2 (sigmoid must exist before calibration writes temperature).\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) calibrate_join_threshold returns None for <5 observations. (B) For 10+ observations with known bimodal distribution, returns a threshold near the valley. (C) Calibrated threshold is written as :policy/concept-join-threshold datom. (D) Temperature is written as :policy/concept-sigmoid-temperature datom. (E) Observe command reads the calibrated values on next invocation. (F) Harvest output reports the calibration.\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/harvest.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs" :op :assert}
